Jul 23 2009 	A simple bed for the night	The Jane is fine for the simple traveler who won't be spending any time in their room.The single rooms are tiny - not enough room to change your mind - but full wall mirrors make it feel twice its size.The web page ( http://www.thejanenyc.com/ ) is cute and it quite realistic. look at the room photo. It will tell you that the building has a long history as a residence.The shared bathrooms are cleaned regularly and are immaculate! Shampoo, conditioner and body wash are supplied. Lots of hot water. (No sinks in the rooms.) Air-conditioning and flat-screen TV.The staff are friendly and helpful.There is a dance club (well-frequented) on the ground floor, but I heard no noise at any time from my 3rd floor room. Apparently a restaurant will open in the fall of 2009.The neighborhood (West Village) is residential and quiet. Nearby delis and restaurants.The #11 bus (9th and 10th Ave) is a 2-minute walk. The #14 bus (14th street) a moment further, and the 8th Ave subway (at 14th) less than 10-minutes on foot.I booked by internet and was given a reasonable price. I checked several days before arriving and the web page advertised a (more recent) lower price. I phoned and they gave me the lower price without any discussion.Conclusion: a simple bed for the night, nothing more. But if that's what you are looking for, it is fine.	
