Jul 21 2009 	Awesome place to sleep for a few nights in the biggest of cities!	Let's face it, you don't go to the Big Apple to sit around in a big hotel room suite all day, right? Yes, the room is really small. Yes, the bed is incredibly small, especially if there's more than one person in the room. Yes, you have to share a bathroom with other guests. But for $99 a night, or less, you have probably the best bargain in Manhattan. And even though the rooms are small and the bathrooms are shared, they are both immaculately kept. I literally saw the bathroom being cleaned every time I used it. I will stay here every time I visit New York, and they will be adding larger rooms in the future, if they haven't already, with private bathrooms and queen and king sized beds. The front desk person was always very helpful as well and the location was close to subways and dining and drinking. While it may not have all the ammenities as other hotels, The Jane is a great place for singles who won't be spending a lot of time in their room, you just have to know what you're getting into before you go.	
