Jun 23 2009 	West Village shabby chic charm	Great for single travellers on a tight budget who don't want to compromise on location, you're just ten minutes walk from the A, C, E and L trains at 8th Ave/14th St subway station and a tree-lined street or two from the delights of the West Village (Sex &amp; The City's Magnolia Bakery is very near), and the designer boutiques of the Meat Packing District.The Jane has bags of West Village shabby chic charm. The rooms, or &quot;cabins&quot;, are certainly small, but so well designed that I never felt cramped. They're very well appointed with air conditioning, fan, flat screen TV/DVD, iPod dock, safe and more than adequate storage. And with the whole of NYC waiting outside, you're not going to be spending much time awake in your room in any case.Some may baulk at the thought of using shared facilities, but this was never a problem for me. The stylish retro black and white tiled bathrooms were always very clean, and I never had to wait to use them. There was always ample hot water and great, powerful showers. The white waffle robes and slippers are a nice touch.My only minor gripes were that the cabins got very hot and stuffy, but in such a small staff the air conditioning unit was so loud as to make listening to music or watching television impossible. Also, although this is a non-smoking hotel I often smelt cigarette smoke in the hallways - this however is more of a problem with fellow guests rather than The Jane istself.All the staff were very polite, friendly and helpful. Even the old-style elevator is charming! As a lone, but independent, female traveller exploring NYC for the first time I found The Jane, although still mid-refurbishment, to be an excellent base, and I would recommend it to anyone needing a safe, secure single room in the city.	
