May 28 2009 	When all you need is a clean place to stay	The Jane is an interesting hotel and lives up to it's micro-hotel status. The abundance of wood in the decor gives it the feel of an older ship and seems to blend in with the atmosphere of the surrounding Manhattan area. Although the rooms are about the size of a large walk-in closet and equipped with a twin size bed, they are clean, comfortable and full of storage space. A flat screen TV and DVD player is found in the room as well, along with an adequate heating/cooling system. It's definitely the kind of place to stay if you are not looking to spend a lot of time in your room and really just want a clean place to stay at a low cost. The communal bathroom is located down the hall with two showers, two sinks, and two toilets. The facilites are definitely clean and I found it no real hassle to walk down the hall to access them. The staff was exceptionally friendly and accomodating to all of my needs.	
